cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of different head structures in R-CNN based detectors, which involves machine learning techniques such as classification and regression. This suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also analyzes the weight matrix in the fully connected head and proposes a new method, which involves natural language processing techniques such as naming and describing objects. This suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the MS COCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark for object detection. This suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible sub-category.
